# ============================================================
# DEPRECATED / LEGACY CONTENT — KEPT ON PURPOSE (v8.4.0 decision)
# ============================================================
# These directories are kept visible (not ignored) to document the project's
# evolution from v7 → v8.4.0. Future contributors and AI agents should SEE the
# legacy code to understand what was removed, why, and what replaced it.
#
# Each `_deprecated/` subdirectory has its own README.md explaining its content.
# Use `git log --follow <file>` to trace moves and decisions across versions.
#
# Decision rationale (2026-06-23, user-mandated):
#   "laisse les deprecated pour qu'ils comprennent que je reviens de loin"
#   — leaving the journey visible is part of the project's narrative.
# ============================================================
# DO NOT add `_deprecated/` to this file. If you want to ignore a NEW
# _deprecated subdir, add a specific exception to this comment block.

# Runtime logs (daemon stdout/stderr, watchdog, MCP server)
